@Sandwich12345: Actually, there are important ways this differs from Terramorphic Expanse.  

1. The card enters play untapped with this cycle. The Expanse brings you a tapped land. Important for keeping up mana tempo.  
2. The Expanse can only bring you a basic land. This cycle isn't so constrained. Notice that it only says "Forest or Island", NOT "Basic Forest or Island". So you can potentially get things like [Breeding Pool](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Breeding Pool), [Tropical Island](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Tropical Island), [Dryad Arbor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dryad Arbor), [Moonring Island](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Moonring Island), or [Sapseep Forest](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sapseep Forest). Those first two are the really important ones.
